title: Sidewall - Fragments, 1955-41-4-a,b, 1900–10
provenance: From the "Upstairs East" room of West College, Williamstown, Massachusetts,built 1796.
creditline: Gift of Mrs. Henry N. Flynt
description: a) beneath "b", ungrounded paper on which is printed a ladder stripe with flowers, alternating with a stripe diapered with lozenges, and a plain stripe. b) Squares in blue and white, two types of foliate decoration which alternate on brown ungrounded paper. Squares are in rows separated by spaces.
